    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Based on the specially formatted number <var>numberstring</var>, you need to output the number divided by two in that same special format.<br><br>The <strong>special format rules</strong>: a number is always represented as a <const>string</const> with length <const>19</const>, which represents a float with 9 numbers before and 6 numbers after the decimal point. All numbers before the decimal point are comma-separated for every three digits, while all numbers after the decimal point are point-separated for every three digits. All positions not used are represented with <const>x</const>.<br><br><strong>For example</strong>: the input <const>xxx,x38,858.321.82x</const> is <const>38858.32182</const>. Divided by two this gives <const>19429.16091</const>, so the output should be <const>xxx,x19,429.160.91x</const>.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1</strong>: the string <var>numberstring</var> with length <const>19</const>, representing a number in special format.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">A string with length <const>19</const>, which is the number from the input, divided by two, in special format.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><var>numberstring</var>  represents a number &gt;= 0 and &lt;= 999999999.999998<br>The last character of <var>numberstring</var> will always either be <const>x</const> or an even number.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">200,000,000.000.002</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">100,000,000.000.001</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
